  "hadith0": "\"The most beloved deeds to Allah are those done consistently, even if small.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith1": "\"Take up good deeds only as much as you are able, for the best deeds are those done consistently even if they are few.\"\n— Ibn Majah",
  "hadith2": "\"When the son of Adam dies, his deeds come to an end except three: ongoing charity, beneficial knowledge, or a righteous child who prays for him.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith3": "\"Whoever prays the two cool prayers (Fajr and Asr) will enter Paradise.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith4": "\"Allah does not look at your appearance or your wealth, but He looks at your hearts and your deeds.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith5": "\"The best of people are those who are most beneficial to people.\"\n— Tabarani",
  "hadith6": "\"Make things easy and do not make them difficult; give glad tidings and do not scare people away.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith7": "\"He who treads a path in search of knowledge, Allah will make easy for him the path to Paradise.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith8": "\"Charity does not decrease wealth.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith9": "\"The strong believer is better and more beloved to Allah than the weak believer, while there is good in both.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith10": "\"Whoever says 'SubhanAllah wa bihamdihi' a hundred times a day will have his sins forgiven even if they were like the foam of the sea.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith11": "\"The best supplication is that of the Day of Arafah, and the best thing that I and the Prophets before me said is: La ilaha illallah.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith12": "\"Whoever recites Ayat al-Kursi after every obligatory prayer, nothing prevents him from entering Paradise except death.\"\n— Nasa'i",
  "hadith13": "\"A good word is charity.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith14": "\"Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him speak good or remain silent.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith15": "\"The one who looks after a widow or a poor person is like a warrior in the cause of Allah.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith16": "\"Smiling at your brother is an act of charity.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith17": "\"The best among you are those who learn the Quran and teach it.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith18": "\"No one has eaten better food than what he earns from the work of his own hands.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith19": "\"Allah is gentle and loves gentleness in all things.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
