  "hadith20": "\"Whoever fasts Ramadan out of faith and seeking reward, his past sins will be forgiven.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith21": "\"Prayer is the pillar of religion.\"\n— Bayhaqi",
  "hadith22": "\"The supplication between the adhan and iqamah is not rejected.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith23": "\"Whoever builds a mosque for Allah, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith24": "\"The best rows for men are the first rows, and the best rows for women are the last rows.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith25": "\"Fasting is a shield from the Hellfire.\"\n— Nasa'i",
  "hadith26": "\"Whoever prays twelve rak'ahs of Sunnah, a house will be built for him in Paradise.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith27": "\"The one who is proficient in the Quran will be with the noble angels.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith28": "\"Seeking knowledge is an obligation upon every Muslim.\"\n— Ibn Majah",
  "hadith29": "\"The best of charity is giving water to drink.\"\n— Ahmad",
  "hadith30": "\"Whoever removes a hardship from a believer, Allah will remove a hardship from him on the Day of Judgment.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith31": "\"The merciful are shown mercy by the Most Merciful.\"\n— Abu Dawud & Tirmidhi",
  "hadith32": "\"Modesty is part of faith.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith33": "\"Cleanliness is half of faith.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith34": "\"Whoever is patient, Allah will give him patience.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith35": "\"The best wealth is a tongue that remembers Allah.\"\n— Tabarani",
  "hadith36": "\"None of you truly believes until he loves for his brother what he loves for himself.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith37": "\"Feed the hungry, visit the sick, and free the captives.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith38": "\"The strong person is not the one who wrestles, but the one who controls himself in anger.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith39": "\"Whoever guards what is between his jaws and his legs, I guarantee him Paradise.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith40": "\"Say 'SubhanAllah', 'Alhamdulillah', and 'Allahu Akbar' thirty-three times each after every prayer.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith41": "\"The best dhikr is La ilaha illallah.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith42": "\"There are two blessings which many people waste: health and free time.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith43": "\"Make use of five before five: youth before old age, health before sickness, wealth before poverty, free time before busyness, and life before death.\"\n— Hakim",
  "hadith44": "\"Whoever recites Surah Al-Ikhlas ten times, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise.\"\n— Ahmad",
  "hadith45": "\"The best prayer after the obligatory prayers is the night prayer.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith46": "\"Charity extinguishes sins as water extinguishes fire.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith47": "\"The one who maintains family ties is not the one who reciprocates. It is the one who maintains them even when cut off.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith48": "\"Every good deed is charity.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith49": "\"Whoever eats food and says: 'Praise be to Allah who has fed me this and provided it without any power or strength on my part,' his past sins will be forgiven.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith50": "\"The most beloved people to Allah are those who are most beneficial to others.\"\n— Tabarani",
  "hadith51": "\"Whoever controls his anger while able to act, Allah will call him before all creation on the Day of Judgment to choose his reward.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith52": "\"Give charity without delay, for it stands in the way of calamity.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith53": "\"Do not belittle any good deed, even meeting your brother with a cheerful face.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith54": "\"The best of you are those who are best to their families.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith55": "\"Whoever recites the last two verses of Surah Al-Baqarah at night, they will suffice him.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith56": "\"The world is a provision, and the best provision is a righteous wife.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith57": "\"Three supplications are never rejected: the supplication of a fasting person, a just ruler, and the oppressed.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith58": "\"Whoever sends blessings upon me once, Allah will send blessings upon him tenfold.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith59": "\"The mosque is the house of every pious person.\"\n— Tabarani",
  "hadith60": "\"Whoever says 'La hawla wa la quwwata illa billah' — it is a remedy for ninety-nine diseases, the least of which is worry.\"\n— Hakim",
  "hadith61": "\"Allah loves that when you do something, you do it with excellence.\"\n— Tabarani",
  "hadith62": "\"Paradise lies under the feet of mothers.\"\n— Nasa'i",
  "hadith63": "\"The most beloved deeds to Allah: prayer at its proper time, then kindness to parents, then jihad in the cause of Allah.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith64": "\"Whoever is thankful for little will be given much.\"\n— Bayhaqi",
  "hadith65": "\"The believer is the mirror of the believer.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith66": "\"Truthfulness leads to righteousness, and righteousness leads to Paradise.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith67": "\"Return the trust to the one who entrusted you, and do not betray the one who betrayed you.\"\n— Abu Dawud & Tirmidhi",
  "hadith68": "\"No fatigue, disease, sorrow, sadness, hurt, or distress befalls a Muslim, even a prick of a thorn, except that Allah removes some of his sins thereby.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith69": "\"The supplication of a Muslim for his brother in his absence is always answered.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith70": "\"Whoever asks Allah for Paradise three times, Paradise says: O Allah, admit him to Paradise.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith71": "\"The most virtuous fast after Ramadan is fasting in the month of Allah, Muharram.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith72": "\"Whoever performs Hajj and does not commit any obscenity or sin returns like the day his mother bore him.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith73": "\"Umrah to Umrah is an expiation for what is between them.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith74": "\"Hasten to do good deeds before trials come like portions of a dark night.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith75": "\"The two rak'ahs of Fajr are better than the world and everything in it.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith76": "\"Whoever says 'Astaghfirullah' regularly, Allah will provide a way out of every difficulty.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith77": "\"If you relied on Allah as He should be relied upon, He would provide for you as He provides for the birds.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith78": "\"Whoever visits a sick person is in the harvest of Paradise until he returns.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith79": "\"Spread peace, feed the hungry, and pray at night when others sleep — you will enter Paradise in peace.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith80": "\"Whoever is not grateful to people is not grateful to Allah.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith81": "\"Envy is not permissible except in two cases: a man to whom Allah has given wealth and he spends it in the right way, and a man to whom Allah has given wisdom and he judges and teaches with it.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith82": "\"A person is upon the religion of his close friend, so let each of you look at whom he befriends.\"\n— Abu Dawud & Tirmidhi",
  "hadith83": "\"Remember death often, for it purifies the heart.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith84": "\"The best of worship is awaiting relief.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith85": "\"Whoever leaves something for the sake of Allah, Allah will replace it with something better.\"\n— Ahmad",
  "hadith86": "\"Whoever conceals the faults of a Muslim, Allah will conceal his faults on the Day of Judgment.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith87": "\"Be in this world as if you were a stranger or a traveler.\"\n— Bukhari",
  "hadith88": "\"Whoever makes it easy for someone in difficulty, Allah will make it easy for him in this world and the hereafter.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith89": "\"The reward of deeds depends upon the intentions.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith90": "\"Avoid suspicion, for suspicion is the most false of speech.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim",
  "hadith91": "\"Whoever gives up lying for the sake of Allah, even while joking, I guarantee him a palace in the outskirts of Paradise.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith92": "\"The doors of goodness are many: glorifying Allah, praising Him, charity, enjoining good, and removing harm from the road.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith93": "\"Eat together and mention the name of Allah, and it will be blessed for you.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith94": "\"The best gathering is the most spacious.\"\n— Abu Dawud",
  "hadith95": "\"Forgive and you will be forgiven.\"\n— Ahmad",
  "hadith96": "\"Tie your camel and then put your trust in Allah.\"\n— Tirmidhi",
  "hadith97": "\"Wondrous is the affair of the believer — everything is good for him.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith98": "\"A Muslim is a brother to a Muslim: he does not wrong him, nor abandon him, nor despise him.\"\n— Muslim",
  "hadith99": "\"The most beloved speech to Allah is: SubhanAllahi wa bihamdihi, SubhanAllahil Azeem.\"\n— Bukhari & Muslim"
}
